metadata.editComments:
Something I want to mention real quick: When you look up the common pop progression I-V-vi-IV on here, you also find songs like this where it's IV-I-V-vi, and you also find vi-IV-I-V.

While it's true they do have the same chords, and each of those progressions can be found within each other if they're looped, they sound quite different depending on which one starts the phrase. 

I think it's misleading to label these progressions as all being the exact same. Even the Axis of Awesome did this in their I-V-vi-IV song. I wish more people knew about that when they watch that video.
